    <abstract>
      <para>This is a vegetation survey dataset of ancient deciduous broadleaved forests in temperate Europe. It contains plot data of the herb layer collected in the framework of the Forest Microclimate Assessment (&lt;a href="https://formica.ugent.be/"&gt;FORMICA&lt;/a&gt;) project.  In total, 125 vegetation relevées of 3x3 m² were surveyed across four gradients:</para>
      <para>1. Macroclimatic gradient from Italy to Norway</para>
      <para>2. Elevational gradient</para>
      <para>3. Gradient of management types (unthinned, thinned 5–10 years ago and recently thinned)</para>
      <para>4. 100m edge-to-interior gradient</para>
      <para>This study was funded by the European Research Council (ERC) (ERC Starting Grant FORMICA 757833).</para>
      <para>For more information on the methodology (and the observed patterns along the edge to core gradients), see Govaert et al. (2019, &lt;a href="http://doi.org/10.1111/jvs.12844"&gt;http://doi.org/10.1111/jvs.12844&lt;/a&gt;).</para>
    </abstract>
